name: seafloor-bathymetry-image-of-north-of-santa-rosa-island-channel-islands-national-marine-sanctuac0c73
notes: This image represents an 8 meter resolution bathymetry of the seafloor north of Santa Rosa Island in Channel Islands National Marine Sanctuary. It was acquired using the ME70 multibeam sonar system onboard the NOAA ship Bell M. Shimada in March of 2015. Data is in UTM zone 10 north, datum WGS84. All users should individually evaluate the suitability of this data according to their own needs and standards.
